        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Semantic hierarchy construction aims to build structures of concepts \r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "linked by hypernym-hyponym (\"is-a\") relations . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "A major challenge for this task is the automatic discovery of such relations . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This paper proposes a novel and effective method for the construction of semantic hierarchies \r",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "based on word embeddings , \r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "which can be used to measure the semantic relationship between words . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "We identify \r",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "whether a candidate word pair has hypernym-hyponym relation \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "by using the word-embedding-based semantic projections between words and their hypernyms . <S>\r",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Our result , an F-score of 73.74 % , outperforms the state-of-the-art methods on a manually labeled test dataset . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Moreover , combining our method with a previous manually-built hierarchy extension method can further improve F-score to 80.29 % . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        }
    ]
